>  This is a non-centralized mechansim based on flooding the network with
>  your real public key and checking it frequently enough to notice an
>  attempt to alter it.

The two obvious problems are 'flooding the network' (bandwidth) and
denial of service attacks in which you (upon seeing two or more
claimed public keys for a given person) decide not to trust anything
allegedly from the sender.

